    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: PulseBoard Channel Plugin\n\n**7 new files** to create under `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files modified.\n\n### Files & Key Decisions\n\n| File | Pattern Source | Notes |\n|------|---------------|-------|\n| `package.json` | `extensions/nostr/package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, ESM, full `openclaw` block |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `extensions/nostr/openclaw.plugin.json` | Minimal empty configSchema |\n| `src/types.ts` | (pure types) | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` with `\"PulseBoard runtime not initialized\"` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with stub adapters + `attachedResults` outbound |\n| `index.ts` | `extensions/irc/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` with `ChannelPlugin` cast |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `extensions/irc/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### Key Design Notes\n\n1. **`getChatChannelMeta`** — imported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (confirmed re-exported there), called as `getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\" as ...)` with a type cast since `\"pulseboard\"` isn't a known registered ID\n2. **`outbound`** — uses the `base` + `attachedResults` structure: `sendText` returns `{ to, messageId }`, and the framework appends `channel: \"pulseboard\"` automatically — giving the full result the user specified\n3. **`PluginRuntime`** — imported directly from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (no local barrel needed for a minimal stub plugin)\n4. **`config` stub** — minimal `listAccounts: () => []`, `resolveAccount: () => null`, `isConfigured: () => false` to satisfy the `ChannelPlugin` contract",
